{{ja-kanjitab|yomi=k|くま}}

From {{inh|ja|ojp|sort=くま|-}}. First cited in the ''{{w|Kojiki}}'' of 712.<ref name="KDJ">{{R:Kokugo Dai Jiten}}</ref>

Further derivation is uncertain. Possibilities include:
* Might be cognate with {{cog|ja|隈|tr=kuma||inside corner; inner bend; hollow or hole in something}}, perhaps from the way that bears often live in [[den]]s.<ref>[http://www.nihonjiten.com/data/45905.html Entry at Nihon Jiten] (in Japanese)</ref>
* Might also or separately be cognate with {{cog|okm|곰〯|tr=kwǒm|t=bear}}, whose archaic form {{IPAfont|*/koma/}} is preserved as the first element of the [[toponym]] {{m|okm|고마〮ᄂᆞᄅᆞ|tr=Kwòmánòlò|lit=Bear-ford}}. Thus, a cognate of {{cog|ko|곰|t=bear}} and {{cog|pkc|金馬|tr=*kəma/*kuma|t=bear}}.
* Might be an [[areal]] [[Appendix:Glossary#wanderwort|Wanderwort]], borrowed from {{cog|och|-}} {{och-l|熊|tr= *C.ɢʷəm}} and ultimately deriving from {{cog|sit-pro|*tV-wəm}}. See also the etymology notes in the {{m|sit-pro|*tV-wəm}} entry.

